title: Burning Man lifts lockdown, says 'exodus' from muddy venue is  underway
description: Organizers lifted a virtual lockdown for the annual Burning Man festival Monday, allowing attendees' annual "exodus" to begin after a weekend of rain and mud isolated the Nevada desert venue.

title: Elon Musk blames ADL for lost revenue, says he's 'against anti-Semitism of any kind'
description: Elon Musk posted that he was against antisemitism Monday and blamed the Anti-Defamation League for lost advertising revenue since his acquisition of X, the platform formerly known as Twitter.

title: Electric Zoo attendees frustrated by chaos at disorganized three-day festival
description: Electric Zoo, the three-day electronic music festival held on Randall's Island, in New York, over Labor Day weekend, was plagued by production and capacity issues, leaving patrons disgruntled.

title: Smash Mouth singer Steve Harwell, known for hit song 'All Star,' dies at 56
description: Smash Mouth lead singer Steve Harwell died Monday at his home in Boise, Idaho.

title: Biden ramps up contrasts with Trump during Labor Day speech in Philadelphia
description: President Joe Biden laced a Labor Day speech Monday in Philadelphia with several pointed attacks at former President Donald Trump.

title: A shake-up and a breakthrough? Ukraine's counteroffensive is at a key moment
description: Ukrainian Defense Minister Oleksii Reznikov submitted his resignation on Monday in a shake-up that comes as the military breached Russia's first defensive line in the south.

title: Putin's education 'indoctrination' and trans legislator's celebrity turn: Morning Rundown
description: In today’s newsletter: The CEO of Burning Man told NBC News that despite rain and mud causing chaos, the annual festival was under control.

title: From 'Sleepy Joe' to 'Crooked Joe': Trump tries to redraw his portrait of Biden
description: Former President Donald Trump has flipped from "Sleepy Joe" to "Crooked Joe," changing his portrayal of his political rival as he faces multiple indictments.

title: Barred from freezing their eggs at home, single Chinese women are traveling elsewhere
description: Single women from mainland China, barred from freezing their eggs at home, are traveling to Hong Kong and elsewhere to undergo the procedure.

title: Jimmy Buffett died after a 4-year fight with a rare skin cancer
description: Jimmy Buffett, whose sun-drenched songs celebrated life by the shore, died of a rare, aggressive skin cancer, according to a statement on his website.
